From: Sam Tobin-Hochstadt <samth@ccs.neu.edu>
To: sk@cs.brown.edu, bugs@racket-lang.org
Cc: nobody@racket-lang.org, bug-notification@racket-lang.org
Subject: Re: [racket-bug] all/11210: signatures need to decide on capitalization
Date: Tue, 14 Sep 2010 09:10:16 -0400

 On Tue, Sep 14, 2010 at 8:08 AM,  <sk@cs.brown.edu> wrote:
 >
 > Right now signatures have TWO conventions:
 >
 > - For defined structures, use the name of the struct.
 > - For pre-defined signatures, use init caps (String, Number, etc).
 
 This is also the convention for Typed Racket.  All types are have
 Initial-Capitals, except structs which are traditionally lowercased.
 I've been unhappy with this inconsistency, but I haven't found a good
 alternative.  It might be possible to have
 
 (struct: foo ([x : Any])
 
 also define `Foo' as the type (or signature) name, but that seems
 unexpected and not in keeping with the rest of the language.  But I
 don't have a better suggestion.
 -- 
 sam th
 samth@ccs.neu.edu
