Subject: Re: [racket-bug] all/11210: signatures need to decide on capitalization
Date: Tue, 14 Sep 2010 08:30:45 -0500

 Yes, thanks. I meant that in Shriram's example below "Foo" becomes the
 type/signature name.
 
 But another problem with this is that not all language have a notion
 of capital letter, so our convention would have to be flexible enough
 to accomodate the case where capitalizing a word does not change the
 word. That seems doable, tho (and likely a source of Chinese in our
 test cases ;).
 
 Robby
 
