Subject: Re: [racket-bug] all/11210: signatures need to decide on capitalization
Date: Wed, 15 Sep 2010 08:05:22 -0400

 > Having different type variables allows you to talk about signatures of
 > things like fold, where two different type variables occur.
 
 You're only discussing the many *correct* cases.  The fact that you
 can write the WRONG contract and it works just the same is a turn-off.
 At least with my students, it would be a disaster.  I don't think a
 formal system should strongly hint at distinctions it can't support.
 
 Shriram
