 Did you not read what I wrote in parens?  I do not believe in it and
 therefore cannot defend it?
 
 I believe your proposal is that I'm supposed to teach with it, have a
 mess in class, then gather statistics, do some kind of validity test,
 and then you will believe me, but not before that?  (Even then, why
 would you believe me?  You'd argue I messed up the lecture on purpose,
 so maybe another person should teach the same audience to be sure.)
 
 This part of contracts is, on its face, broken.  The burden's on the
 person who puts out the broken thing, just like if Matthew were to
 decide tomorrow that GC is overrated or safety checks are overrated,
 and he's taking them away.
 
 The rest of the contract system is not broken -- it's working very
 nicely, actually!  I'm happy to have experimented with it.
 
 Shriram
 
